    • batchTimeIt

      public static TimeResult batchTimeIt(Runnable function, int batchSize)
      Given a runnable funtion returns a TimeResult object with all the values of time spent running that function. The amount of times that the function is executed is defined by batchSize. If batchSize is invalid input: '<'= 0, returns a Duration of 0.
      Parameters:
      function - to run
      batchSize - Amount of times that the function will be executed
      Returns:
      TimeResult with the durations of each execution
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if batchSize invalid input: '<'= 0

      public static TimeResult[] batchTimeIt(Runnable[] functions, int batchSize)
      Given a runnable funtion array returns a TimeResult object array with the mean value of time spent running each function. The amount of times that a function is executed is defined by batchSize. If batchSize is invalid input: '<'= 0, returns a Duration of 0.
      Parameters:

      batchSize - Amount of times that each function will be executed
      Returns:
